verbose_text: In addition, miR-195 was found to inhibit the proliferation, migration and invasion of cervical cancer cells by targeting SMAD family member 3 (Smad3), cyclin D2 (CCND2), MYB proto-oncogene, transcription factor (MYB) and cyclin D1.
